According to FWC, sporadic blooming has been reported in the areas of Pinellas, Mentee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier County, indicating a decrease in concentrations.
The area of the flowering sea stretches about 130 miles coast from Pinellas County in the north to Lee County in the south.
The flourishing surfaces occur about 10 miles from the Hillsborough district coast, but to less places than last week.
Sea flowering has also been recorded in Pasco County.
In the past week, average concentrations in the district of Pinellas, low to high concentrations in the coastal region of Hillsborough, average to high concentrations in the district of Manatee, average to high concentrations in the district of Sarasota or its coastal region, average to mean concentrations in the district of Charlotte, average to high concentrations in the district of Lee or its coastal region, and low concentrations in the district of Collier.
Cases of irritable airways continue to occur in the districts of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier.
During the past week, no cases of irritability of airways have been reported in Northwest Florida.
